    <detaileddescription>
<para>Different type to mark <ref refid="sync_8h_1a326d1d46ce05b5316d8ebe2694a10a6e" kindref="member">Mutex</ref> at global scope</para>
<para>Thread safety analysis can&apos;t handle negative assertions about mutexes with global scope well, so mark them with a separate type, and eventually move all the mutexes into classes so they are not globally visible.</para>
<para>See: <ulink url="https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/pull/20272#issuecomment-720755781">https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/pull/20272#issuecomment-720755781</ulink> </para>
